    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="946"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d946">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.00/3136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-11T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 11, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>257. My 234, March 31, 2 p.m. and Department’s 118, April 1. midnight. In
                    conversation with Secretary General of Foreign Office, I informed him of
                    contents of Department’s telegram of March 25, to Thurston.<note n="53"
                        xml:id="d946fn53">Telegram No. 139, <ref target="#pg_827">p.
                        827</ref>.</note> I emphasized that it had been made clear to Vyshinsky by
                    Thurston that American Government was not in a position to <pb facs="0842"
                        n="830" xml:id="pg_830"/> confirm the report, could not be responsible for
                    its authenticity, and desired that no public reference which might be made to
                    the report should indicate that it had come through an American source.</p>
                <p>Numan Bey expressed his appreciation and dismissed the matter casually with the
                    remark that Vyshinsky had obviously exaggerated in his talk with the Turkish
                    Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Kuibyshev.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
